# onchain (default) mode - SPACER_MODE unset. Reads are snapshot-served (doc 15): the refresh_snapshots precondition reads arbiter/src/bitcoin.py against the fake bitcoin-cli at $BITCOIN_CLI_BIN, and the petcli read itself never touches a backend; write variants stop at the recipient-address-registry / standing-approvals gates or the not_implemented dispatch stub before reaching bitcoin.py; Lightning- and eCash-extension ops refuse at the mode gate (decision_refuse_mode). arbiter/src/lnd.py and arbiter/src/ecash.py are never imported in this mode (the runner asserts both). No live bitcoind / LND / mint traffic for any variant in the current manifest.
